    },
    {
      "id": "8505c5b993e9ab130373d27a34fe8fe926b43fe8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2017-11-18 19:32:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(3 comments)\n\nI thought about reducing the size cl_page but I found it difficult to reach the target without significant code change. We need to make sure the new page buffer is under 256 bytes otherwise it won't help much.\n\nWith current data structure, the size of cl_page is still over 256 bytes even after removing log_page and lovsub_page. The size of cl_page will be 80(cl_page) + 64(vvp_page) + 200(osc_page) = 344 bytes. We need to reduce osc_page for sure.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "6e8e5df18c57131616e2b3a0d4eb687f53e76994",
      "author": {
