      },
      "date": "2017-11-19 02:33:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> I thought about reducing the size cl_page but I found it difficult to reach the target without significant code change. We need to make sure the new page buffer is under 256 bytes otherwise it won't help much.\n\nYes, I have been looking at this. This is only the first in the series. But I wanted to make sure that you and Mike didn't need these layers for future flr or dom work. OSC definately has the most fat. But as you say there is redundancy all around.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
