    {
      "id": "5151309b681681fa688dcf6fd3b5350754d3da71",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2017-12-11 14:28:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nI have moved the cl_lock changes to https://review.whamcloud.com/30192.\n\n> it chages default cl_lock_enqueue() behavior from returning -ENOSYS in case of missed enqueues in slices to returning OK silently. Is that safe? Wouldn't it be better to keep the old behavior if we have no reasons to change it?\n\nChanging the default return value allows us to remove the nop lock slices.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "6a4450d9b29b20a77d985ba0666951ffb49f03b8",
